<TD><a style="color: #990099; text-decoration: none; background: none">
 
Perception filters over an individuals human mind appear in layers. Well what has placed them there? They're exsistence is not constrained to the three dimensional space and time that your mind is still constrained by at this stage. Some of them exsist as a property of the human mind and some of these layers exsist as products of an individuals personal 'incorporation'<p>  

Look, it's a bit like this. You can only see the chair in black and white because of the perception filter that has been placed over your optical sensors unbeknown to you. You can't see the filter. You do not know that the filter even exists. You are never likely to suggest that there is more to the chairs exsistence than what you already percieve of it. Someone comes along and tells you that there is more to the chair than meets your eyes. Being very open minded to the suggestion you inquire further into what that may in fact be. They, in all their infinite wisdom, inform you that the chair does possess a very strange and wonderful property indeed.<p> 

'Wow'. 'What does it look like?' You exclaim in absolute amazement.<p>

'Oh', they say..... 'really, um.... er...., <a href="colour.htm" TITLE= "The extra dimension is of course only our ability to resolve light within the visible band we we refer to as colour, but the word colour, would of course remain entirely meaningless to you as it is something of which you have never previously had any experience, whatsoever. Your esteemed friend has therefore deemed any reference to the term colour, being a word in itself an entity completely unknowable, as completely superfluous and unnecessary.">wonderful</a>?

