 See my point?<p>

I'll go on to suggest that this person is also someone held in very high regard. And so you wander around telling everyone that he says 'all material things possess a very rich and wonderful property which we can not see'! And so they too are most interested as to what this thing could be. They are not aware that you possess the optical perception filter that you do. They hold the information that you now communicate to them in very high regard also.<p>
'Wow'. They remark. 'There is more to reality than that of which we are aware. And it is really wonderful!' They suggest total amazement at what it must be like!<p>

There upon they make their consultation with 'The man' and beseech of him to reveal more about this 'new' and 'wonderful' imerceptible dimension possessed of by all there is that does be. <p>

'Show it to us' they implore with their impassioned yearnings for that which is more about everything there is.<p>

'But I can not!' must necessarily by his most earnest repose indeed of needs become.<p>

'But we must know where we can come by such an is this new and wonderful faculty' <p>

'It was only that of mans ability to resolve the <i>colour</i> in all things to which it was I did refer when speaking with this one who can see the things in life only through the light in shades of black and white.<p>


